\begin_layout Abstract
The dynamics of an electronic system interacting with an electromagnetic
 field is investigated within mixed quantum-classical theory.
 Based on the analysis of quantum–classical Liouville equations and the
 standard Ehrenfest equation of motion, we propose a new 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Ehrenfest+R
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 method, incorporating complementary quantum transitions to account for
 quantum effects that are lost in the mean-field approximation.
 The method recover the spontaneous emission rate and reveal the incoherent
 emission of a two-level electronic system.
 We explore the method to treat resonance Raman scattering, highlighting
 the power of Ehrenfest+R approach.
\end_layout

