\end_layout

\end_inset

First, it is well-known that, for electron–nuclei dynamics, Ehrenfest or
 mean-field dynamics does not satisfy detailed balance
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "parandekar_detailed_2006"

\end_inset

.
 This drawback may cause incorrect electronic populations at long times.
 The failure of maintaining detailed balance leads to anomalous energy flow
 that may violate thermodynamics at equilibrium
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "jain_vibrational_2018"

\end_inset

.
 For electron–radiation dynamics, this problem may not be fatal since the
 absorption and emission of radiation field can be considered relatively
 fast in time compared to electron–nuclei dynamics.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Note Note
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
